6 - @Lazy annotation - 
    When we bootstrap(means start the application) by default spring creates all singleton beans eagerly for the 
	classes where we use stereo type annotations.

    You can create the spring bean lazily(on demand) by using @lazy annotation.
    the class in which we use @Lazy annotation creates the bean of that class on demand(means). @Lazy can be used 
	with @Configuration, @Component and @Bean.
	
	Note : Eager initialization is recommended at the time we start the application.@Lazy is not recommended.
	
