Q : What is acid properties? 
Ans : 
ACID = Set of rules to make sure database transactions are reliable.
A – Atomicity
➤ All or nothing.
→ A transaction either completes fully or doesn't happen at all.

C – Consistency
➤ Valid state.
→ Data must be correct before and after the transaction.

I – Isolation
➤ No mixing.
→ Transactions don’t affect each other, even when run at the same time.

D – Durability
➤ Permanent.
→ Once a transaction is done, the changes stay even if system crashes.

🧠 Example: Sending money from one bank account to another:

Amount is deducted from one → Atomic

Total balance stays correct → Consistent

No clash if two users send at same time → Isolated

If server crashes after transfer → Still saved → Durable


