Ans : In a typical Spring Boot project, we add important dependencies like spring-boot-starter-web for building REST APIs,
spring-boot-starter-data-jpa for database operations, the database driver like mysql-connector-java, 
spring-boot-starter-test for JUnit and Mockito testing, and lombok to reduce boilerplate code.

1. Spring Boot Starter Web – for REST APIs / web apps
   This gives you support for building REST APIs, controllers, and handling HTTP requests.

2. Spring Boot Starter Data JPA – for database communication
   Helps you work with databases easily using JPA/Hibernate.

3. Database Driver (like MySQL) – to connect to DB
   Without this, your application can’t connect to MySQL (or whichever DB you’re using).

4. Spring Boot Starter Test – for JUnit & Mockito
   Includes JUnit, Mockito, and other testing tools.

5. Lombok – to reduce boilerplate code (getters/setters)
   Auto-generates getters, setters, constructors, etc., and makes your entity classes cleaner.

6. Validation – if you’re doing request validation
   Needed if you use @Valid, @NotNull, @Email, etc.
   




    
























	
